2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses enhancing the protocol to improve fairness and throughput. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses a protocol that uses hysteresis to sustain high throughput. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the impact of the protocol on multimedia applications. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses a protocol for contention resolution in a distributed system.
